CLI commands

pwd: print working directory- where you are in the computer
mkdir: creates a new directory/folder
cd: change directory
cd ..: go back one action
ls: list the contents in the current directory
touch: create a new file
mv: move file/folder
cp: copy file/folder
grep: find 
echo: display lines of text or string which are passed as arguments on the command line
cmd + k: clear the terminal
ctrl + a: take cursor to the beginning of line
ctrl + e: take cursor to the end of the line
ctrl + u: clear the input line
ctrl + c: abort current task and regain user control
option + click to the area: takes cursor to the part of line you want to type input
cat: print the content of a file onto 
